My friends and I went to this sushi place hoping to relax, eat and overall have a good time which we did, but we were all disappointed with our final payment there since it seemed like a rip-off. A part of it may be because we were young, but I personally can say on behalf of my friends that we know when something seems fishy. There were around 13 people, and our final price came out to over $300 including tax. On top of that $300, we were forced to pay $43 in tips which seemed ridiculous to us considering the fact that there service wasn’t worth that much. If anything I believed we were scammed out of because tips aren’t NECESSARY, they're called ‘’tips’’ for a reason. I wouldn’t recommend the general public to this place, it was a waste of our time, and eating cheap pizza would’ve been 10x better.  Would've rated this 0 stars if I could.

I think I ate the wrong dressing, so I can't attest to how good it is.  My recent delivery was weird. The delivery driver tried to avoid bringing up my order.  He called me to come outside. I could hardly understand him. I buzzed him up, and no one came. A few seconds later the restaurant called me saying he was outside. I explained to them that he has to buzz and come up. He did.  I prepaid on my credit card, including gratuity. The delivery driver pinched his fingers (which were filthy) in front of me and screamed "Money."  I told him I prepaid, but he didn't seem to understand. He gestured at me again before leaving.  That was unsettling, so I called the restaurant and asked them to explain to him that my tip was already paid. They said they would. I should have told them not to give it to him based on his behavior.
